<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[264,1324,804,1110]" box="[264,366,804,829]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[264,366,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[264,1324,804,1110]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[473,622,844,870]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1980) Studies on neotropical water mites. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 31, 1 - 645." type="journal article" year="1980">
Cook (
<number box="[552,613,844,870]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
the number of acetabula on one genital plate varies from 
<number pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6­ 7</number>
. In my specimens this number varies between 
<number box="[850,893,884,910]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5­6</number>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1219,884,909]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Dodecabates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dodecaporus">
<emphasis box="[905,1219,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Dodecabates dodecaporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread, and has been found along the Andes from the Jujuy Province in the north to the Neuquén Province in the south. Moreover, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[772,921,964,990]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1980) Studies on neotropical water mites. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 31, 1 - 645." type="journal article" year="1980">
Cook (
<number box="[852,913,964,990]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
collected the species in the Sierra de la Ventana, Buenos Aires Province, and Rosso de Ferradás (
<number box="[1031,1093,1004,1030]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2000.0">2000</number>
) collected it in the Sierra de Córdoba. The new record presented here from Chubut Province extends its range further south.
</paragraph>
